# Business Card Scanner - Process Flow

## Overview

This document outlines the complete end-to-end process flow for the Business Card Scanner application, from image capture to contact storage.

---

## High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    User[User] --> Frontend[React Frontend]
    Frontend --> Camera[Camera Capture]
    Frontend --> Upload[File Upload]
    Camera --> Backend[FastAPI Backend]
    Upload --> Backend
    Backend --> OCR[Florence-2-base OCR]
    Backend --> Parser[Hybrid Parser]
    OCR --> Parser
    Parser --> LLM[Qwen LLM]
    Parser --> Regex[Regex Extraction]
    LLM --> Merge[Data Merger]
    Regex --> Merge
    Merge --> Validation[Validation]
    Validation --> DB[(Supabase DB)]
    DB --> Frontend
```

---

## Detailed Process Flows

### 1. Single-Side Card Scanning Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant C as Camera/Upload
    participant B as Backend API
    participant O as Florence-2 OCR
    participant P as Hybrid Parser
    participant L as Qwen LLM
    participant R as Regex Engine
    participant D as Database

    U->>F: Open App
    F->>U: Display Upload Options
    
    alt Mobile Camera
        U->>C: Click "Open Camera"
        C->>U: Show In-Browser Camera
        U->>C: Capture Photo
        C->>F: Return Image File
    else File Upload
        U->>C: Drag & Drop / Browse
        C->>F: Return Image File
    end
    
    F->>B: POST /scan-card (image)
    B->>O: Process Image
    O->>O: Extract Text (OCR)
    O->>B: Raw OCR Text
    
    B->>P: parse_card_text_hybrid(text)
    
    par Parallel Extraction
        P->>R: Extract Structured Fields
        R->>R: Phone, Email, Website, Zip
        R->>P: Structured Data
    and
        P->>L: Extract Semantic Fields
        L->>L: Name, Title, Company
        L->>P: Semantic Data
    end
    
    P->>P: Merge & Validate Data
    P->>B: Parsed Contact Data
    
    B->>F: JSON Response
    F->>U: Display Extracted Data
    
    U->>F: Review & Edit (optional)
    U->>F: Click "Save Contact"
    F->>D: Save to Supabase
    D->>F: Confirmation
    F->>U: Success Message
```

---

### 2. Dual-Side Card Scanning Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant C as Camera/Upload
    participant B as Backend API
    participant O as Florence-2 OCR
    participant P as Parser
    participant M as Merger
    participant D as Database

    U->>F: Select "Both Sides" Mode
    F->>U: Prompt for Front Side
    
    U->>C: Upload/Capture Front
    C->>F: Front Image Stored
    F->>U: Show "Front ✓"
    
    F->>U: Prompt for Back Side
    U->>C: Upload/Capture Back
    C->>F: Back Image Stored
    F->>U: Show "Front ✓ Back ✓"
    
    F->>B: POST /scan-card-dual (front, back)
    
    par Process Both Sides
        B->>O: OCR Front Image
        O->>O: Extract Front Text
        O->>B: Front OCR Text
    and
        B->>O: OCR Back Image
        O->>O: Extract Back Text
        O->>B: Back OCR Text
    end
    
    B->>P: Parse Front Text
    P->>B: Front Data
    
    B->>P: Parse Back Text
    P->>B: Back Data
    
    B->>M: merge_card_data(front, back)
    M->>M: Apply Priority Rules
    M->>M: Validate Merged Data
    M->>B: Merged Contact Data
    
    B->>F: JSON Response
    F->>U: Display Merged Data
    
    U->>F: Click "Save Contact"
    F->>D: Save to Database
    D->>F: Confirmation
    F->>U: Success Message
```

---

## Component-Level Process Details

### A. Frontend Camera Capture Process

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle: App Loaded
    Idle --> CameraRequested: User Clicks "Open Camera"
    CameraRequested --> PermissionCheck: Request getUserMedia
    
    PermissionCheck --> CameraActive: Permission Granted
    PermissionCheck --> PermissionDenied: Permission Denied
    
    CameraActive --> Capturing: User Clicks Capture
    Capturing --> Preview: Photo Captured
    
    Preview --> Retake: User Clicks Retake
    Preview --> Processing: User Clicks "Use Photo"
    
    Retake --> CameraActive
    Processing --> Uploading: Convert to File
    Uploading --> [*]: Send to Backend
    
    PermissionDenied --> [*]: Show Error
```

**Steps:**
1. User clicks "Open Camera" button
2. Browser requests camera permission via `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia()`
3. If granted, video stream starts in full-screen overlay
4. User can toggle front/back camera
5. User clicks capture button
6. Canvas captures current video frame
7. Preview shows captured image
8. User can retake or confirm
9. On confirm, image converted to JPEG File object
10. File sent to processing pipeline

---

### B. Backend OCR Processing

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Image File] --> B[Load Image]
    B --> C[Resize to 1024x1024]
    C --> D[Florence-2-base Model]
    D --> E[OCR Task]
    E --> F[Extract Text]
    F --> G[Post-process]
    G --> H[Raw OCR Text]
```

**Process:**
1. Receive image file from frontend
2. Load image using PIL
3. Resize to max 1024x1024 (maintain aspect ratio)
4. Convert to RGB
5. Pass to Florence-2-base model with `<OCR>` task
6. Model generates text with bounding boxes
7. Extract text content
8. Return raw OCR text string

**Performance:** ~3-7 seconds on CPU

---

### C. Hybrid Parser Process

```mermaid
graph TB
    Start[Raw OCR Text] --> Split{Split Processing}
    
    Split --> Regex[Regex Extraction]
    Split --> LLM[LLM Extraction]
    
    Regex --> RegexPhone[Extract Phones]
    Regex --> RegexEmail[Extract Emails]
    Regex --> RegexWeb[Extract Websites]
    Regex --> RegexZip[Extract Zip Codes]
    Regex --> RegexAddr[Extract Addresses]
    
    LLM --> Prompt[Build Context-Aware Prompt]
    Prompt --> Generate[Generate Response]
    Generate --> Parse[Parse JSON]
    Parse --> LLMName[Extract Names]
    Parse --> LLMTitle[Extract Job Title]
    Parse --> LLMCompany[Extract Company]
    
    RegexPhone --> Merge[Merge Results]
    RegexEmail --> Merge
    RegexWeb --> Merge
    RegexZip --> Merge
    RegexAddr --> Merge
    LLMName --> Merge
    LLMTitle --> Merge
    LLMCompany --> Merge
    
    Merge --> Validate[Validate & Clean]
    Validate --> Output[Final Contact Data]
```

**Steps:**

**Phase 1: Regex Extraction (Fast)**
1. Extract phone numbers (validate 10-15 digits)
2. Extract email addresses
3. Extract website URLs
4. Extract zip codes (5 digits only)
5. Extract addresses using location keywords
6. Remove extracted data from text

**Phase 2: LLM Extraction (Accurate)**
1. Build context string from regex results
2. Create prompt with:
   - Field definitions (context awareness)
   - Extraction rules
   - Examples
   - Remaining text
3. Send to Qwen-2.5-1.5B model (512 tokens)
4. Parse JSON response
5. Extract first_name, last_name, job_title, company_name

**Phase 3: Merge & Validate**
1. Combine regex + LLM results
2. Validate phone numbers (not zip codes)
3. Clean and normalize data
4. Return complete contact object

**Performance:** ~5-10 seconds total

---

### D. Dual-Side Merge Process

```mermaid
graph TB
    Front[Front Side Data] --> Compare{Compare Fields}
    Back[Back Side Data] --> Compare
    
    Compare --> Name[Merge Names]
    Compare --> Contact[Merge Contact Info]
    Compare --> Address[Merge Address]
    Compare --> Company[Merge Company]
    
    Name --> Priority1{Front Priority}
    Contact --> Priority2{Field-Specific Logic}
    Address --> Priority3{More Complete}
    Company --> Priority4{Front Priority}
    
    Priority1 --> Merged[Merged Data]
    Priority2 --> Merged
    Priority3 --> Merged
    Priority4 --> Merged
    
    Merged --> Validate{Validate}
    Validate --> Final[Final Contact]
```

**Merge Rules:**
1. **Names**: Front side priority (usually person name on back)
2. **Company**: Front side priority (company name typically on front)
3. **Contact Info**: Field-specific:
   - Email: Use non-empty value
   - Phone: Distinguish mobile vs work
   - Website: Use non-empty value
4. **Address**: Choose more complete address
5. **Raw Text**: Combine both with [FRONT]/[BACK] markers

**Validation:**
- Ensure at least name OR company exists
- Ensure at least one contact method exists
- Warn if critical data missing

---

## Data Flow Summary

### Input → Output Transformation

```
User Image
    ↓
[Florence-2-base OCR]
    ↓
Raw Text: "PITCH MY VENTURE\nChandni Nagda\nFOUNDER\n+91 99675 28901\nchandni@pitchmyventure.com"
    ↓
[Hybrid Parser]
    ↓
Regex Extracts:
- email: "chandni@pitchmyventure.com"
- mobile_phone: "+91 99675 28901"
    ↓
LLM Extracts (with context):
- first_name: "Chandni"
- last_name: "Nagda"
- job_title: "FOUNDER"
- company_name: "PITCH MY VENTURE"
    ↓
[Merge & Validate]
    ↓
Final Contact JSON:
{
  "first_name": "Chandni",
  "last_name": "Nagda",
  "job_title": "FOUNDER",
  "company_name": "PITCH MY VENTURE",
  "email": "chandni@pitchmyventure.com",
  "mobile_phone": "+91 99675 28901",
  "website": "",
  ...
}
    ↓
[Save to Supabase]
    ↓
Contact Saved in Database
```

